    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document specifies the Forwarding and Control Element Separation (ForCES) protocol.  The ForCES protocol is used for communications between Control Elements (CEs) and Forwarding Elements (FEs) in a ForCES Network Element (ForCES NE).  This specification is intended to meet the ForCES protocol requirements defined in RFC 3654.  Besides the ForCES protocol, this specification also defines the requirements for the Transport Mapping Layer (TML). [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
